&lt;p&gt;Notwithstanding the details shown on the drawings hereby approved, detailed drawings showing the following modifications to the scheme must be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority, in writing, before any work is commenced:
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a) the first floor rear extension is finished in matching brick&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
b) the replacement windows on the rear elevation shall be sash units and match the design of the existing windows of the original building and be finished in timber frames&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

These parts of the development may only be undertaken in accordance with the modifications thus approved and retained thereafter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: To protect the design character and appearance of the original building, and the wider Conservation Area.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Save for condition 3, the Development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
REASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.
&lt;/p&gt;
